    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1093.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 19, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 2d of Sep tember, transmitting a copy of a note of the
                            20th of July last, addressed to you by our consul at Cape Town,
                            communicating the facts in regard to the non-restoration of the
                            Tuscaloosa to her rightful owners. It seems necessary to inform her
                            Britannic Majesty’s government that this government is unable to
                            acquiesce in the disposition of the subject which that government has
                            made.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
